<div id = "basics">
    <h1>CSS Basics</h1>
    You can learn more about CSS here : <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/css/" 
    target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.w3schools.com/css/</a>
    I have built a very simple HTML page with CSS. Check the different elements and the form.
    Here is our primitive example: <a href="/basic/basiccss.html">Basic CSS</a>
 
    <pre>
    <code class="lang-html">
    &lth1&gtThis a HTML page with CSS example&lt/h1&gt

    &ltdiv class=""&gt
        &ltp&gtThanks so much for visiting this site!&lt/p&gt
    &lt/div&gt
    
    &lth2&gtWhat is this site for?&lt/h2&gt
    &ltp&gtThis site can do three things:&lt/p&gt
    &ltol&gt
        &ltli id='itemone'&gtTake in text input&lt/li&gt
        &ltli&gtTake in Log In Information&lt/li&gt
        &ltli&gt&lta href="http://www.google.com" target="_blank" &gtTake you to Google&lt/a&gt&lt/li&gt
    &lt/ol&gt
    
    &ltdiv class="blogtext"&gt
        &lttextarea name="name" id="textblock"&gt&lt/textarea&gt
    &lt/div&gt       
    &lth2&gtPlease log in to save your blog post&lt/h2&gt       
    &ltform class="loginForm" method="get"&gt
        &ltlabel for="mail"&gtEmail: &lt/label&gt
        &ltinput type="email" id="mail" value=""&gt       
        &ltlabel for="pass"&gtPassword: &lt/label&gt
        &ltinput type="password" id="pass" value=""&gt        
        &ltinput type="submit" name="" value="Log In"&gt                
    &lt/form&gt
    
    &ltdiv class="exit"&gt     
        &ltp&gtQuestions or Comments? Send us feedback here:&lt/p&gt
        &lttextarea name="name" rows="8" cols="80"&gt&lt/textarea&gt 
    &lt/div&gt    
    </code>
    </pre>
    <pre><code class="lang-css">
    /*h1 have a 1px solid black border*/
    h1{
        border: 1px solid black;
    }
    
    /* h2 elements has purple color, font-family: sans-serif*/
    h2{
        font-family: sans-serif;
        color: purple;
    }
    
    /*Input boxes have a 2px solid dark red border*/
    input{
        border: 2px solid rgb(144, 0, 0);
    }
    
    /*paragraphs ha yellow backgroud color*/
    div p{
        background:#fffca5;
    }
    
    /*Set Text box set a width,a height and border*/
    
    #textblock{
        border: 4px solid gray;
        width: 600px;
        height: 300px;
    }
    
    /*There is a link to Google on the page. This link is red.*/
    a{
        color: red;
    }
    
    /*The id="itemone" have an overline text-decoration and the color is purple.*/
    #itemone{
        text-decoration: overline;
        color: purple;
    }
    
    /*The "exit" class have a background of blue and a 4px dashed yellow border.*/
    .exit{
        background-color: blue;
        border: 4px dashed yellow;
    }
    
    /* There is a link to Google on the page in the list. I have changed the color if it is clicked */
    a:visited{
        color:blue
    }
                 
    </code></pre>

