<div id = "fonts">
    <h1>Fonts</h1>  
    In <b>CSS</b> you can use different fonts with the <b>font-family</b> attribute:
    <pre><code class="lang-css">
    h1{
        font-family: cursive;
    }
        
    p{   
        font-family: monospace;
    }
    </code></pre>

    If you use own font files, you have to set a <b>font-face</b>
    <pre><code class="lang-css">
    @font-face{
        font-family: your_font_name;
        src: url(path/to/woff_file.woff);
    }
    </code></pre> 
    You can download fonts from the internet or you can use them from a remote CDN with a link reference in the 
    head section in the HTML file.
    <pre><code class="lang-html">
    &ltlink href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Bree+Serif" rel="stylesheet"&gt   
    </code></pre> 
</div>


<div id ="icons">
<h1>Icons</h1>
    We can use icons in our application. Icons are fonts.
    We have chosen two different font types. The first is 
    <a href="https://fontawesome.com/how-to-use/on-the-web/setup/getting-started?using=web-fonts-with-css" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Font Awesome</a> 
    for this purpose. As mentioned on that website, you can use them from their CDN. We have decided to download them. <br>
    The other one is <a href="https://icomoon.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">IcoMoon</a>. <br>
    First we have put the font files in our <b>assets/fonts</b> folder and the <b>css</b> files in the <b>assets/styles</b> folder. <br>
    <img src="/images/fonts.jpg"> <br>
    It is important to set the right folders in the <b>CSS</b> files of the font files. So, in the <b>solid.css</b> and <b>icomoon.css</b> 
    you have to set the <b>assets/folder</b>. I have renamed the <b>styles.css</b> of the <b>icomoon</b> fonts to <b>icomoon.css</b>. 
    <pre><code class="lang-css">
    /* Icomoon.css */
    @font-face {
        font-family: 'icomoon';
        src:  url('../fonts/icomoon.eot?k56r01');
        src:  url('../fonts/icomoon.eot?k56r01#iefix') format('embedded-opentype'),
        url('../fonts/icomoon.ttf?k56r01') format('truetype'),
        url('../fonts/icomoon.woff?k56r01') format('woff'),
        url('../fonts/icomoon.svg?k56r01#icomoon') format('svg');
        font-weight: normal;
        font-style: normal;
    }
    
    /* solid.css */
    @font-face {
        font-family: 'Font Awesome 5 Free';
        font-style: normal;
        font-weight: 900;
        src: url("../fonts/fa-solid-900.eot");
        src: url("../fonts/fa-solid-900.eot?#iefix") format("embedded-opentype"), 
        url("../fonts/fa-solid-900.woff2") format("woff2"), 
        url("../fonts/fa-solid-900.woff") format("woff"), 
        url("../fonts/fa-solid-900.ttf") format("truetype"), 
        url("../fonts/fa-solid-900.svg#fontawesome") format("svg"); }
    </code></pre>

    Next import the <b>css</b> files into the <b>styles.css</b>
    <pre><code class="lang-css">
    @import 'assets/styles/icomoon.css';
    @import 'assets/styles/solid.css';
    @import 'assets/styles/brands.css';
    @import 'assets/styles/fontawesome.min.css';
    </code></pre>

