    <h1>SCSS</h1>
    SCSS is an CSS extension language, a preprocessor. With the help of it,  it is easier to write CSS code. 
    The browsers does not understand SCSS, so you have to complie it to CSS. For example with <b>node-saas</b> compiler. To install it: <br>
    <b>npm install -g node-sass</b> <br>
    Or make it on the fly with this npm module. Follow these steps: <br>
    <ul>
        <li>In the project folder : <b>npm install --save compile-sass</b></li>
        <li>In the <b>server.js</b> file: <br>
        <pre><code class="lang-javascript">
            const compileSass = require('compile-sass');
            const path = require('path');

            app.use('/css/:cssName', compileSass({
            sassFilePath: path.join(__dirname, '/scss/'),
            sassFileExt: 'scss',
            embedSrcMapInProd: true
            }));

        </code></pre>
